SIMPLE: monosepalous
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Monosepalous
<hw>Mon`o*sep"al*ous</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos>
<ety>[<ets>Mono-</ets> + <ets>sepal</ets>: cf. F.
<ets>monos⟦eacute⟧pale</ets>.]</ety> <fld>(Bot.)</fld> <def>Having only
one sepal, or the calyx in one piece or composed of the sepals united
into one piece; gamosepalous.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><note>⟦hand⟧ The most recent writers restrict this term to flowers
having a solarity sepal, and use <contr>gamosepalous</contr> for a calyx
formed by several sepals combined into one piece. Cf.
<er>Monopetalous</er>.</note>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>monosodium glutamate</ent>⟦br⟧
